1
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:02,520
Hang in there.

2
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:05,840
I know it hurts. Hang in there.

3
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:12,560
Come on. I'll untie you.

4
00:02:17,200 --> 00:02:18,040
Does it hurt?

5
00:02:20,960 --> 00:02:22,320
Those traffickers should rot in hell!

6
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:23,240
They should rot!

7
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,960
<i>They all deserve it! They all do!</i>

8
00:02:26,600 --> 00:02:27,440
<i>That kid.</i>

9
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,000
Why did he go to your place after?

10
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:33,360
Pony, he told me

11
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:35,400
his parents always fought.

12
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:38,440
He didn't want to go home.

13
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:43,040
He asked me if I could take him in.

14
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:06,840
Come on. Have a bit more.

15
00:03:09,440 --> 00:03:10,520
Thanks, Daddy Peng.

16
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:21,000
Pony.

17
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:28,520
Eat up. Here.

18
00:03:40,520 --> 00:03:43,440
- Thanks, Daddy Peng.
- You're welcome.

19
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:55,120
<i>CHINESE HISTORY, GRADE 8 VOL.2</i>

20
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:12,920
Daddy Peng.

21
00:04:13,640 --> 00:04:15,120
I'm going back to school today.

22
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:18,120
Okay. Then after school, I'll pick you up.

23
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,000
No need.

24
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,720
I haven't been home for days.

25
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:22,160
My parents must be worried.

26
00:04:26,440 --> 00:04:27,760
I won't come here anymore.

27
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:30,560
Daddy Peng, thanks for taking care of me.

28
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,440
Dad's here.

29
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,560
This is your home.

30
00:04:50,640 --> 00:04:51,680
From now on,

31
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:54,160
focus on your studies
and keep up with your homework.

32
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,840
As for school,
you don't need to go anymore.

33
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,680
This is your home.

34
00:05:02,440 --> 00:05:03,840
I'll teach you at home.

35
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:07,840
Pony is too young. He doesn't understand.

36
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:11,040
He has no idea how I feel as his dad.

37
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:14,720
What I fear most is that
he'll run away again someday.

38
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,600
Then what am I supposed to do?

39
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:18,280
What am I supposed to do?

40
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:21,480
That's why I need to keep more ponies.

41
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:23,160
So I can feel at ease.

42
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:42,920
Going to an internet cafe?

43
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:44,880
I'll give you a ride.

44
00:05:48,840 --> 00:05:50,280
No charge. Get in.

45
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,840
Thanks, sir.

46
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,520
Eat.

47
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,480
Do you want to stay over tonight?

48
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:05,880
Huh?

49
00:06:05,960 --> 00:06:08,120
I run a Trojan Horse Hotel here.
It's upstairs.

50
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,440
I… I don't have money.

51
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:13,440
No need to pay. Free.

52
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,560
It's convenient
both upstairs and downstairs.

53
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,800
Everything's right here.
Do whatever you like.

54
00:06:17,880 --> 00:06:19,000
Sounds good.

55
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:20,200
Sounds good.

56
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,200
- That's nice!
- Nice!

57
00:06:22,280 --> 00:06:23,120
Eat.

58
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:26,040
One pony.

59
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,480
Two ponies.

60
00:06:29,400 --> 00:06:30,840
Three ponies.

61
00:06:31,520 --> 00:06:33,080
Four ponies.

62
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,240
I have four ponies.

63
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,840
I cook for them every day.

64
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:41,480
<i>I study with them</i>
<i>and teach them how to behave.</i>

65
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,640
What about Han Zi'ang?

66
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:45,760
What's wrong with him?

67
00:06:53,320 --> 00:06:54,880
This pony is too disobedient.

68
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,720
Too disobedient. Too disobedient!

69
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,400
Too disobedient.

70
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,960
You must be starving. Eat up.

71
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,200
Thanks, sir.

72
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:10,880
My mom already cooked.

73
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:12,080
She's waiting at home.

74
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:48,280
Help! Help!

75
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,160
YUANLONGLI INTERNATIONAL GARDEN

76
00:08:58,240 --> 00:08:59,440
You're back?

77
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:01,120
You're back.

78
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,000
Peng is weird. Why's he ignoring me?

79
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,400
- Right.
- No idea.

80
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:16,760
"If life deceives you…"

81
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,640
"If life deceives you…"

82
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:25,560
"…don't be sad, don't be anxious."

83
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:29,520
"…don't be sad, don't be anxious."

84
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:30,920
"Believe it,

85
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,320
- the happy days…"
- Daddy Peng,

86
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:35,200
I need the bathroom.

87
00:09:42,120 --> 00:09:43,400
Go ahead.

88
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:49,680
Come on. Let's continue.

89
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:54,040
"The heart always longs for the future."

90
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:57,600
"The heart always longs for the future."

91
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:01,000
"Now is often full of sorrow."

92
00:10:11,840 --> 00:10:14,480
Pony, where's the bathroom?

93
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:18,960
Let go of me! You bad guy!

94
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:25,240
You bit me! How dare you bite me!

95
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,680
That's for biting me! Try that again!

96
00:10:28,560 --> 00:10:29,680
I swear I'll kill you.

97
00:10:31,760 --> 00:10:33,240
You never listen. Serves you right.

98
00:10:38,280 --> 00:10:39,120
Dad…

99
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:41,120
Dad…

100
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,600
- Dad…
- Pony?

101
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,360
Pony? You're back!

102
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,840
Pony!

103
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:14,440
I missed you!

104
00:11:15,480 --> 00:11:18,200
I missed you!

105
00:11:22,720 --> 00:11:25,520
My pony!

106
00:11:35,480 --> 00:11:36,320
Good work.

107
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:39,120
Leave the rest to us.

108
00:12:01,760 --> 00:12:03,000
I've been looking for you everywhere.

109
00:12:03,080 --> 00:12:04,560
How'd you end up here?

110
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:07,480
Listen, you did a great job today.

111
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,480
Director Zou just called.

112
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:12,480
He said he'll be highlighting

113
00:12:12,560 --> 00:12:15,680
He Xiaohe at the case briefing.

114
00:12:15,760 --> 00:12:18,080
He also granted our task force
three days off.

115
00:12:21,080 --> 00:12:23,240
What's wrong?

116
00:12:25,320 --> 00:12:26,280
Something on your mind?

117
00:12:28,240 --> 00:12:31,400
Peng Dachuang may be alive,

118
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:37,320
but he never really
made it out of that fire.

119
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:42,360
He tried everything
to make it up to his son.

120
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:45,040
He's completely consumed by it.

121
00:12:52,280 --> 00:12:54,800
I remember Captain Ran mentioned
a theory in his book.

122
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:56,920
It's called "the domino effect".

123
00:12:57,000 --> 00:13:01,960
In this case,
a lot of seemingly unrelated events

124
00:13:02,040 --> 00:13:05,680
are actually like dominoes
spaced far apart.

125
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:09,480
Maybe the first domino to fall

126
00:13:09,560 --> 00:13:11,480
was Peng Dachuang's son.

127
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:19,440
Family is… a strange thing.

128
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:23,720
When everything's fine,
people start looking for trouble,

129
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,000
like they have to break it somehow.

130
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,680
But if it's missing a piece,

131
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,720
people try hard to fix it.

132
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:46,680
I never thought I'd become a cop.

133
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:50,960
But when Uncle Ran was gone,

134
00:13:52,760 --> 00:13:54,040
my family felt incomplete.

135
00:13:56,120 --> 00:13:57,320
I wanted to fix it.

136
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:05,760
Among all these lit windows,

137
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:11,040
if one belonged to Uncle Ran,

138
00:14:13,800 --> 00:14:15,000
that'd be nice.

139
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:34,120
SONG QINGSONG, DUE TO COLLUSION
BETWEEN WU SHANLONG AND ZHAO HONGMEI

140
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,280
WROTE A RANSOM LETTER IN XU MENG'S NAME

141
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:36,440
FURTHER USING XU MENG'S DEATH

142
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,760
AND THE LEAKED DONGSHAN MINE BID
TO FORCE SONG QINGSONG OUT OF WEIYANG

143
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:41,040
<i>After the Mount Wu accident,</i>

144
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,680
<i>Xu Meng, to pay</i>
<i>for her father's treatment,</i>

145
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:46,800
<i>went to Yuanlongli and worked</i>
<i>at Pattia as a masseuse.</i>

146
00:14:46,880 --> 00:14:50,360
<i>That decision was like the first domino</i>

147
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,320
<i>in a long chain to fall,</i>

148
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:54,600
<i>setting off a chain reaction.</i>

149
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:19,880
Had a nightmare?

150
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,280
What time is it?

151
00:15:25,760 --> 00:15:27,840
- Is the report done yet?
- Almost done.

152
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,760
Perfect. Take a look
and give me your thoughts.

153
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:36,680
I'm not used to this. Print it out later.

154
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:43,160
Sir, we've gone paperless
at the bureau now,

155
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,520
and there's a new
office automation system too.

156
00:15:45,600 --> 00:15:47,200
I got you an account set up.

157
00:15:47,280 --> 00:15:49,400
The username is your full name in pinyin,

158
00:15:49,480 --> 00:15:51,840
- and the password is…
- What system or whatever,

159
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,480
I don't get it.

160
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:58,280
Me and this computer
just don't get each other.

161
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,200
Whoever wants it can use it.

162
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,800
THE JUNE 30TH CASE HAS MULTIPLE SUSPECTS
AND TANGLED LEADS…

163
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:20,360
With Song Qingsong's jump,
the June 30th case has to be closed.

164
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:23,960
I never thought my first case

165
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:26,480
would end like this with a full stop.

166
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:28,640
At best, it's just a pause.

167
00:16:29,160 --> 00:16:31,600
As for Xu Meng, her body's still missing.

168
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:39,360
Maybe one day,
her remains will surface again.

169
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:43,160
When that happens,
don't you start crying again.

170
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,560
Sir,

171
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:50,760
if it weren't for you
scolding me back then,

172
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:53,240
I'd probably be a teacher now.

173
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,200
Good that you know.

174
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:04,640
By the way, sir,

175
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,160
I've already filed a request

176
00:17:06,240 --> 00:17:08,640
to transfer you
to the administrative department.

177
00:17:13,599 --> 00:17:14,720
It's a new department,

178
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,040
not much workload, so you can spend
more time with Xiaohe.

179
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:25,800
Sounds good.

180
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:33,000
This little troublemaker
used to skip class every day.

181
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:36,600
Winter break's coming.
Might as well help her with her studies.

182
00:17:39,040 --> 00:17:39,920
Sounds good.

183
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:43,560
Let's go. Let's grab some rice noodles.

184
00:17:45,120 --> 00:17:48,000
I haven't finished the report.
Why don't you rest a bit longer?

185
00:17:48,080 --> 00:17:50,120
You want me to keep
having nightmares, right?

186
00:17:50,200 --> 00:17:52,320
- Let's go.
- Coming.

187
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:58,080
Let me remind you,

188
00:17:58,160 --> 00:18:00,360
don't just focus on work.

189
00:18:00,440 --> 00:18:03,040
You need to think
about your personal life too.

190
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,440
I'm not in a rush.

191
00:18:05,520 --> 00:18:06,840
You're not, but I am.

192
00:18:06,920 --> 00:18:09,920
You two, not one of you
gives me peace of mind.

193
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,080
How am I not giving you peace of mind?

194
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:16,520
<i>Let me introduce myself</i>

195
00:18:17,240 --> 00:18:20,400
<i>They call me a beggar…</i>

196
00:18:21,520 --> 00:18:25,680
<i>A flood took both my parents</i>

197
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:29,520
<i>Now I live all alone</i>

198
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:34,920
<i>With a worn-out begging basket</i>

199
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,520
<i>And a bamboo stick to fend off dogs</i>

200
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:44,080
<i>I wander through streets and alleys</i>

201
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,880
<i>Past butcher stalls</i>

202
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,680
<i>And restaurants</i>

203
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:53,280
<i>Pawnshops and bank counters</i>

204
00:18:53,360 --> 00:18:57,560
<i>Calling out to ladies and gentlemen</i>

205
00:18:57,640 --> 00:19:00,240
<i>Have pity on this poor beggar…</i>

206
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:04,560
Young little girl, no spirit,

207
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,560
can't even match an old man.

208
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:11,920
Don't lie there. Come eat
the celebratory noodles.

209
00:19:13,880 --> 00:19:15,880
Just noodles for a celebration?

210
00:19:15,960 --> 00:19:17,520
Not even a bit of oil?

211
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:18,920
So what?

212
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:22,720
Back then, your Uncle Ran and I
celebrated with noodles too.

213
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:25,320
Hurry up. Come here.

214
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:39,440
What are you looking at?
Do I have oil on my face?

215
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:45,080
Dad, have you seen Uncle Ran again lately?

216
00:19:46,360 --> 00:19:47,800
What do you mean?

217
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:50,040
You want me to do therapy again?

218
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:52,800
Drop that idea.

219
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:53,800
I'm telling you,

220
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:57,960
right now, I'm positive and healthy,

221
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,560
better than you young people.

222
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,520
Hurry up. The noodles are getting cold.

223
00:20:01,600 --> 00:20:02,560
Come on.

224
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:06,320
Eat.

225
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:20,720
Everything in here belonged to Uncle Ran.

226
00:20:21,840 --> 00:20:24,760
You weren't really yourself before,
but now that you're better,

227
00:20:25,480 --> 00:20:28,000
I can finally
give these things back to you.

228
00:20:30,160 --> 00:20:32,440
Here, Comrade He Yuanhang.

229
00:21:12,960 --> 00:21:16,240
RETURNED MAIL: NO SUCH PERSON AT ADDRESS

230
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,400
When you retired two years ago,

231
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:20,120
you sent out all these letters.

232
00:21:21,160 --> 00:21:24,240
But they were all returned.

233
00:21:25,120 --> 00:21:27,520
Later, I checked with the registry.

234
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:32,800
They said Uncle Ran's grandma
passed away in 1992.

235
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:45,960
MAIL TO GRANDMA IN SHANDONG

236
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,000
FROM WEIYANG, SICHUAN

237
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:52,920
MAIL TO GRANDMA IN SHANDONG

238
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,120
FROM WEIYANG, SICHUAN

239
00:21:54,200 --> 00:21:55,320
I didn't expect that all those years…

240
00:21:55,400 --> 00:21:56,760
MAIL TO GRANDMA

241
00:21:56,840 --> 00:22:00,800
…Uncle Ran had been writing letters
to his late grandma.

242
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,000
This guy

243
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,400
carries too many people in his heart.

244
00:22:12,040 --> 00:22:15,640
The living and the gone.

245
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:26,760
How come I have no memory of any of this?

246
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,800
It was that day.

247
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:35,720
JUNE 3RD, 2013

248
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:37,040
You suddenly fainted.

249
00:22:38,480 --> 00:22:39,320
After you woke up,

250
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:42,000
you kept saying Uncle Ran
had come back from Beijing.

251
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:44,240
I was terrified.

252
00:22:44,320 --> 00:22:46,480
I was afraid these things
would trigger you again.

253
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,600
CHINA POST, SIGNATURE HE YUANHANG

254
00:22:47,680 --> 00:22:49,640
So I hid them all.

255
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:16,600
This, is there a way
to recover the data inside?

256
00:23:17,880 --> 00:23:18,720
What for?

257
00:23:19,680 --> 00:23:21,960
I want to see if there's anyone left

258
00:23:22,040 --> 00:23:23,840
in your Uncle Ran's hometown
we can contact,

259
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:28,440
so we can send his belongings back.

260
00:23:28,520 --> 00:23:31,720
So he can finally rest where he belongs.

261
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:38,360
This thing is so old,
and it's been burned.

262
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:43,160
Unless… there's some tech genius.

263
00:23:53,480 --> 00:23:58,280
I made you the property manager
to work with me.

264
00:23:58,360 --> 00:23:59,200
And what did you do?

265
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:01,840
You're in league with those holdouts.

266
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:04,080
If I don't pull out the big guns,

267
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,720
how are we tearing
this building down next month?

268
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:06,640
No…

269
00:24:08,240 --> 00:24:09,680
- Officer He?
- Uncle He.

270
00:24:14,960 --> 00:24:17,720
Qian Dajun, what are you up to this time?

271
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,440
Come on.

272
00:24:19,520 --> 00:24:23,760
I'm wholeheartedly thinking
about the community.

273
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:27,200
What you're saying,
the ghosts here might buy that.

274
00:24:27,280 --> 00:24:28,240
I don't.

275
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:33,760
NEW YORK BLOCK

276
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:36,040
Flank him from your side!

277
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:38,240
I'll ambush him! I see him.

278
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:39,800
Lure him over!

279
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:46,200
Uncle He, try another way to say hi.

280
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:47,560
You nearly scared me to death.

281
00:24:47,640 --> 00:24:50,600
If you keep staying up,
you'll be the one dropping dead.

282
00:24:53,320 --> 00:24:54,600
Take a look at this.

283
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:58,040
Is there a way to get
the contacts from this phone?

284
00:24:59,840 --> 00:25:03,080
Uncle He, why did you bring
this burnt brick back to me again?

285
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,040
Didn't I already extract it for you
two years ago?

286
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:07,080
Two years ago?

287
00:25:08,080 --> 00:25:11,480
Two years ago, I worked my tail off.

288
00:25:13,040 --> 00:25:14,760
Why don't I remember any of it?

289
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:17,920
Forget it. Do it for me again.

290
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:19,040
No chance.

291
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:22,880
This thing, once the data was extracted,
the motherboard was fried.

292
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,400
Didn't I email it to you?

293
00:25:26,480 --> 00:25:29,440
All the data is in the attachments.

294
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,360
I don't really get this.

295
00:25:31,440 --> 00:25:33,320
So you emailed me.

296
00:25:33,400 --> 00:25:35,600
Then, the stuff inside,
you didn't keep a copy?

297
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:39,360
When I work, I leave no evidence.

298
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:45,440
Uncle He, what email did you use then?

299
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,480
I think…

300
00:25:50,160 --> 00:25:54,080
I think it had an eye icon.

301
00:25:54,160 --> 00:25:55,200
An eye?

302
00:26:00,040 --> 00:26:01,040
Is this it?

303
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:03,120
Yes! That's it.

304
00:26:03,800 --> 00:26:05,560
The username is my phone number.

305
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:07,640
The password…

306
00:26:08,760 --> 00:26:09,800
The password…

307
00:26:11,120 --> 00:26:12,400
I forgot it.

308
00:26:13,160 --> 00:26:14,440
No problem.

309
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,920
I've got this. Three seconds.

310
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,480
One. Two. Three.

311
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,800
Who cut my power?

312
00:26:24,880 --> 00:26:28,240
Who else could it be?
That heartless creep.

313
00:26:28,320 --> 00:26:30,080
Qian Dajun!

314
00:26:30,160 --> 00:26:31,800
It must be you!

315
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:50,440
Slow down.

316
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:52,440
Easy.

317
00:27:03,200 --> 00:27:05,240
WEIYANG PUBLIC SECURITY BUREAU
NANSHAN BRANCH, YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH CASE

318
00:27:08,280 --> 00:27:11,440
CRIMINAL INVESTIGATION FILES

319
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:18,040
INTERVIEW RECORD

320
00:27:18,120 --> 00:27:20,640
YUANLONGLI JUNE 30TH CASE, SUMMARY REPORT

321
00:27:25,280 --> 00:27:26,680
What's wrong?

322
00:27:26,760 --> 00:27:28,240
The names are reversed.

323
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:29,840
No need.

324
00:27:30,600 --> 00:27:33,280
He, we need to stick to the facts.

325
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:34,400
I'm sticking to the facts.

326
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:37,920
REPORTERS: RAN FANGXU, HE YUANHANG

327
00:27:56,280 --> 00:27:57,960
MENGMENG NO.23

328
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:40,760
MAIL LOGIN

329
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:41,720
INCORRECT USERNAME OR PASSWORD

330
00:28:57,480 --> 00:28:59,680
So early, what are you busy with?

331
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:02,400
Why aren't you at work?

332
00:29:03,320 --> 00:29:06,120
The task force has three days off.
Director Zou approved it.

333
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,360
What's the password for this email?

334
00:29:11,360 --> 00:29:13,080
How did you forget again?

335
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:15,560
Your full name in pinyin,
plus your birthday.

336
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,360
You haven't used it in years.

337
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:21,680
Why get trendy now?

338
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,000
INCORRECT USERNAME OR PASSWORD

339
00:29:27,720 --> 00:29:29,040
Still wrong.

340
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,600
Capitalize the first letter.

341
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:48,240
DU, PHONE RECOVERY

342
00:29:50,240 --> 00:29:53,000
CONTACTS.TXT, TEXTS.TXT, CALL LOG.TXT

343
00:29:56,480 --> 00:29:57,960
CONTACTS.TXT

344
00:29:58,040 --> 00:29:59,480
CONTACT LIST

345
00:29:59,560 --> 00:30:01,560
COUSIN

346
00:30:10,200 --> 00:30:13,680
0535…

347
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,520
32.

348
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:26,760
<i>Hello. The number you dialed is invalid.</i>

349
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:28,720
<i>Please check and dial again.</i>

350
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:39,600
TEXTS

351
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:44,480
DIRECTOR ZOU: DON'T STAY UP

352
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,640
RAN: DON'T STAY UP TONIGHT

353
00:30:45,720 --> 00:30:46,760
<i>Don't stay up tonight.</i>

354
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:48,400
<i>Go home and rest early.</i>

355
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:51,080
<i>I'm fine, senior. I'll leave after work.</i>

356
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,800
<i>That's an order. Go home now.</i>

357
00:30:54,840 --> 00:30:55,680
<i>Copy that.</i>

358
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:59,840
<i>Ran, I saw a sweater today.</i>
<i>It would look good on you.</i>

359
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:00,760
SENDER: QIAO

360
00:31:00,840 --> 00:31:02,560
<i>Are you free this weekend?</i>

361
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:05,200
<i>Sorry, Qiao. I've got to work overtime</i>
<i>this weekend.</i>

362
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:06,720
<i>Maybe next week.</i>

363
00:31:07,320 --> 00:31:09,360
<i>Let's find a day for dinner.</i>

364
00:31:09,440 --> 00:31:12,120
<i>Okay. Don't overwork yourself.</i>

365
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:13,600
<i>Get some rest.</i>

366
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:14,600
<i>Don't worry.</i>

367
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:24,200
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE TO HE YUANHANG

368
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:38,280
Dad, what's wrong?

369
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:41,320
Dad.

370
00:31:55,880 --> 00:31:59,240
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE TO HE YUANHANG

371
00:31:59,320 --> 00:32:04,480
RAN: SIR, THE JUNE 30TH CASE WAS WRONG
ALL WRONG

372
00:32:08,760 --> 00:32:11,120
This message, I never received it.

373
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:13,520
Ran never sent it to me.

374
00:32:14,880 --> 00:32:16,400
The June 30th case?

375
00:32:17,000 --> 00:32:19,400
Isn't that the Xu father-daughter case?

376
00:32:19,480 --> 00:32:21,280
Wasn't it closed long ago?

377
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:24,680
Why would Uncle Ran write this?

378
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:28,960
He must have gone behind my back
to reinvestigate it

379
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,720
and found a major clue.

380
00:32:32,320 --> 00:32:33,280
So major…

381
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:37,040
it could overturn
all previous conclusions.

382
00:32:40,800 --> 00:32:42,880
Dad. Look.

383
00:32:43,880 --> 00:32:46,640
That was the night
something happened to Uncle Ran.

384
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:49,600
But this message
was drafted that afternoon.

385
00:32:57,360 --> 00:32:59,320
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE
SAVE AT 2003-01-31 13:09:37

386
00:33:01,920 --> 00:33:03,760
What was he trying to tell me?

387
00:33:04,680 --> 00:33:06,480
Why didn't he send it?

388
00:33:07,760 --> 00:33:10,320
Ran must have left with deep regrets.

389
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,280
Why didn't I see this email sooner?

390
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,920
PHONE RECOVERY BY DU ON JUNE 3RD, 2013

391
00:33:26,240 --> 00:33:28,840
Dad, I brought food back.

392
00:33:28,920 --> 00:33:30,040
Eat it while it's hot.

393
00:33:36,520 --> 00:33:37,640
Dad?

394
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,800
Dad?

395
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,920
Dad! What did you do? Dad!

396
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:52,720
Don't scare me! Wake up! Dad!

397
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:55,800
What did you do? Dad!

398
00:33:56,320 --> 00:33:58,520
Don't scare me! Dad!

399
00:33:59,480 --> 00:34:00,320
Dad!

400
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,240
JUNE 3RD, 2013

401
00:34:01,320 --> 00:34:02,160
Dad!

402
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:04,320
Dad!

403
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:06,080
PHONE RECOVERY BY DU ON JUNE 3RD, 2013

404
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,360
I get it now.

405
00:34:08,400 --> 00:34:09,239
That time you fainted,

406
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:10,760
it must've been
because you saw this message.

407
00:34:10,840 --> 00:34:13,120
That's why you kept imagining
Uncle Ran had come back.

408
00:34:16,639 --> 00:34:19,880
So, this is the root of your illness.

409
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:25,800
I saw this message two years ago?

410
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:29,600
Dad, think hard again.

411
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,560
After the case was closed,

412
00:34:31,639 --> 00:34:34,520
did Uncle Ran ever mention
the June 30th case again?

413
00:34:40,639 --> 00:34:41,480
Who is it?

414
00:34:42,960 --> 00:34:44,960
Sir, why are you…

415
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,920
What are you doing here?

416
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:52,679
It's the weekend,
and it's the Winter Solstice.

417
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:55,520
I brought Qiao to help
warm up your new place.

418
00:34:56,280 --> 00:34:57,120
Ran.

419
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:01,760
I… I didn't prepare anything.

420
00:35:01,840 --> 00:35:04,120
We're all friends. No need for all that.

421
00:35:05,240 --> 00:35:06,400
Let her in already.

422
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,080
Come in.

423
00:35:09,160 --> 00:35:11,000
The floor is dirty.
No need to change shoes.

424
00:35:16,760 --> 00:35:19,680
Nice place. The bureau treats you well.

425
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:21,720
Just a bit musty.

426
00:35:22,640 --> 00:35:23,480
It needs more life.

427
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:26,240
Have people over more. It'll be fine.

428
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:28,640
I'll get some plants for Ran later on.

429
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:30,800
Sounds good.

430
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:37,600
Don't bother.

431
00:35:37,680 --> 00:35:40,240
You rarely come by. Let's eat downstairs.

432
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:42,600
Why eat at a restaurant?

433
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:44,800
We're not just warming your home,
we're firing up your kitchen too.

434
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:46,840
Qiao said she'd cook for you.

435
00:35:46,920 --> 00:35:48,600
How can you refuse?

436
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,640
How nice.

437
00:36:13,120 --> 00:36:15,840
Oh no. I forgot to pick up Xiaohe.

438
00:36:16,720 --> 00:36:17,600
You two eat first.

439
00:36:19,520 --> 00:36:20,680
Sir.

440
00:36:22,120 --> 00:36:23,440
Today is Sunday.

441
00:36:25,360 --> 00:36:26,320
Is it?

442
00:36:27,880 --> 00:36:29,520
Then she definitely
didn't do her homework.

443
00:36:29,600 --> 00:36:31,880
I need to keep an eye on her. You two eat.

444
00:36:33,040 --> 00:36:34,400
Sir!

445
00:36:38,040 --> 00:36:39,440
I'll… see him out.

446
00:36:41,440 --> 00:36:42,280
Sir!

447
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:46,000
Stay and have a bite with us.

448
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,000
No.

449
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:50,520
She's already putting herself out there.
You should show some interest too.

450
00:36:50,600 --> 00:36:52,360
Qiao is a good girl.

451
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:54,280
Don't let her slip away.

452
00:36:59,040 --> 00:36:59,880
Sir,

453
00:37:00,760 --> 00:37:04,000
how's work in the new department?

454
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:07,760
It's much easier than field duty.

455
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:09,760
I'm thinking of writing

456
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:12,560
something about the June 30th case
when I get the time.

457
00:37:12,640 --> 00:37:14,080
A detailed one.

458
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:16,600
If similar cases come up,
it can be a reference.

459
00:37:18,600 --> 00:37:22,200
Me? All I can do now
is stay in the archives.

460
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,200
I have no choice.

461
00:37:24,280 --> 00:37:27,120
My memory keeps betraying me.

462
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:33,040
Sir, do you remember the blue heels
from the June 30th case?

463
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,680
Blue heels? What about them?

464
00:37:35,920 --> 00:37:37,920
The bureau had a pipe burst the other day.

465
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,120
Water was everywhere.
We spent ages cleaning up.

466
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:44,440
But those blue heels just went missing.

467
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:49,440
Maybe they were cleared out as junk?

468
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:50,840
But the case is already closed.

469
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:53,160
Doesn't matter if they're missing.

470
00:37:55,040 --> 00:37:56,040
Alright. That's far enough.

471
00:37:56,120 --> 00:37:58,080
Qiao is still busy upstairs.

472
00:37:58,160 --> 00:38:00,240
Go help her. I'm off.

473
00:38:03,160 --> 00:38:04,360
Take care.

474
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:13,040
Blue heels.

475
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:15,360
Ran mentioned the blue heels.

476
00:38:15,440 --> 00:38:17,000
What blue heels?

477
00:38:18,080 --> 00:38:20,600
In the June 30th case evidence,
there was a pair of blue heels.

478
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:22,960
They were what Xu Meng was wearing
when she went missing.

479
00:38:23,960 --> 00:38:26,400
Those blue heels
were one of the key pieces

480
00:38:26,480 --> 00:38:28,000
of evidence against Wu Shanlong.

481
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:32,400
Ran mentioned before that
when a pipe burst at the bureau,

482
00:38:32,480 --> 00:38:35,280
he noticed those blue heels were missing.

483
00:38:35,360 --> 00:38:38,480
The shoes went missing.
That doesn't prove anything.

484
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:39,920
How does it not prove anything?

485
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:42,040
It means back then,

486
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:44,200
Ran was already reinvestigating this case.

487
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:45,360
Otherwise, how would he know

488
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,320
that the evidence box
was missing evidence?

489
00:38:49,200 --> 00:38:51,640
You go to the archives right now

490
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:53,840
and check the June 30th case files.

491
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:55,840
See if Ran added any new evidence.

492
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:57,560
Okay.

493
00:39:05,440 --> 00:39:06,560
Dad,

494
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:09,320
do we really need to push
this case this far?

495
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:13,440
These were Uncle Ran's last words.

496
00:39:13,520 --> 00:39:15,160
Do you think we shouldn't push this?

497
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:25,320
DRAFT, UNSENT MESSAGE TO HE YUANHANG

498
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:28,280
RAN: SIR, THE JUNE 30TH CASE WAS WRONG
ALL WRONG

499
00:39:52,560 --> 00:39:55,200
WOODCUT KNIFE
